        <section id="introduction">
            <h1>Long/Sharp Toenails</h1>
            <p>Long and sharp toenails are an alluring feature often found in fetish art, particularly for their sharpness and intense aesthetic appeal. These nails can be seen as symbols of dominance, power, and vulnerability, depending on their portrayal. Artists often use long, sharp nails to emphasize the curvature and sharpness of the feet, creating a blend of sensuality and danger.</p>
            <figure>
                <img src="https://wimg.rule34.xxx//images/2198/84ed3b2134fd9bd8874286d65956ddca.jpeg?11698963" alt="Example of Long/Sharp Toenails">
                <figcaption>Sharp toenails in a sensual and dominant pose. - Art by qizhu</figcaption>
            </figure>
        </section>
        <hr>

        <section id="details">
            <h2>Detailed Descriptions</h2>
            <p>Long and sharp toenails are characterized by their elongated, pointed shapes, often exaggerated for dramatic effect. These toenails may be polished or left bare, depending on the desired aesthetic. The sharpness of the nails creates an intense visual effect, often symbolizing power or danger. Key characteristics include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Length:</strong> Often extended beyond the natural shape of the toe, creating an elegant yet threatening appearance.</li>
                <li><strong>Sharpness:</strong> The nails are often tapered to a fine point, enhancing their visual impact.</li>
                <li><strong>Color:</strong> Typically painted in bold colors such as red, black, or metallics to emphasize their dominance and allure.</li>
                <li><strong>Highlighting:</strong> The nails are often the focal point of the foot, with light and shadow accentuating their sharpness.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <hr>

        <section id="examples">
            <h2>Examples</h2>
            <p>Long and sharp toenails are commonly featured in the following contexts:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Giantess Themes:</strong> The nails are used to emphasize dominance, such as stepping on or crushing small objects.</li>
                <li><strong>Foot Worship:</strong> Often depicted in scenarios where the sharpness of the nails enhances the submissive nature of the interaction.</li>
                <li><strong>Stomping:</strong> Sharp toenails add a level of danger when paired with stomping imagery, heightening the intensity of the scene.</li>
                <li><strong>Roleplay and Fantasy:</strong> Long, sharp toenails create a powerful visual in fantasy settings, symbolizing the dominance and power of the character.</li>
            </ul>
