        <section id="cultural-relevance">
            <h2>Cultural and Artistic Relevance</h2>
            <p>The depiction of long and sharp toenails carries symbolic weight, often representing power, control, and fear. In some cultures, sharp objects are associated with strength, precision, and even danger, all of which are conveyed through these exaggerated features in art and fetish contexts.</p>
        </section>
